{
  "semantic_description": "Counts the number of bytes equal to 101 in a read-only null-terminated character array. The function initializes a scanning pointer p to s, advances p one byte at a time while *p is nonzero, increments count exactly on matching bytes, and returns the total after reaching the unique terminator at index n. The input CharArray::full buffer is preserved and the function does not modify memory.",
